# React Native / Expo Documentation

Use current Expo and React Native docs — do not rely on training data for API details.

## Priority 1: Context7 MCP

Use Context7 `resolve-library-id` then `query-docs`:

| Source | Preferred Context7 library ID |
| --- | --- |
| Expo | `/expo/expo` |
| Expo docs site | `/websites/expo_dev` |
| React Native | `/facebook/react-native` |
| Better Auth (Expo integration) | `/better-auth/better-auth` |

Pass the user's full question as the `query` parameter. Be specific:

- ❌ "Expo Router docs"
- ✅ "Expo Router tabs layout auth redirect protected routes"

## Priority 2: Direct sources (shell fallback)

```bash
# Expo doc indexes
curl -s https://docs.expo.dev/llms.txt
curl -s https://docs.expo.dev/llms-full.txt

# React Native
curl -s https://reactnative.dev/llms.txt

# Better Auth Expo integration
curl -sH "Accept: text/markdown" https://www.better-auth.com/docs/integrations/expo
```

## Repo conventions

- Mobile app: `apps/mobile` — Expo Router, NativeWind, TanStack Query
- Auth: `apps/mobile/src/lib/auth-client.ts` — `better-auth/react` + `@better-auth/expo/client` + `expo-secure-store`
- API data: `apps/mobile/src/lib/api-client.ts` — `@costly/api-client` with cookies from `authClient.getCookie()`
- Env: `EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL` (same value as web `VITE_API_URL`)
- Deep link scheme: `costly` in `app.json`
- UI: custom RN components in `apps/mobile/src/components/` — do not use `@costly/components` (web/Subframe only)

## Notes

- Native fetch does not enforce browser CORS, but session cookies still require the Better Auth Expo plugin.
- For monorepo setup, see Expo docs on [monorepos](https://docs.expo.dev/guides/monorepos/).
- Search Better Auth Expo docs when changing mobile auth or cookie forwarding to the Hono client.
